author: Mike Santa Barbara
title: High School Football: Spartans improve to 4-2, Senators, Riders, and Panthers all fall
text: High School Football: Spartans improve to 4-2, Senators, Riders, and Panthers all fall Comment By Mike Santa Barbara Posted Oct. 16, 2015 @ 10:41 pm Lake Forest 18, Laurel 13 Lake Forest earned their third victory in a row Friday night, defeating Laurel 18-13. Noah Feague-Johnson scored twice on the ground for Lake Forest, while Ben Moore scored the winning touchdown late in the third quarter to preserve the victory for the Spartans. The Spartans are now 4-2 on the season after an 1-2 start to the season. Lake Forest is on the road next week, taking on the Glasgow Dragons Friday night. Dover 14, Cape Henlopen 35 Cape Henlopen took an early 21-0 lead Friday night against Dover, running away with things early on the way to a 35-14 victory over the Senators. Triston Harris connected with Karim Beatty for a Dover touchdown, and Jordan Allen recovered a Cape fumble for a touchdown to round out the Senators’ scoring. With the loss, Dover drops to 3-3 on the season. The Senators are back on the road next week traveling north to take on Salesianum at Baynard Stadium Friday night. Caesar Rodney 6, Sussex Central 28 The Riders fell to 1-5 on the season, losing to Sussex Central Friday night 28-6. The Golden Knights took a slim 7-0 lead into the break, scoring twice more in the third quarter to gain a 21-0 advantage heading into the fourth quarter. The Riders managed a late score trailing 28-0, but there wasn’t enough time to mount a comeback. CR is back in action next Friday night on the road taking on Cape Henlopen. Polytech 14, DMA 45 Polytech fell to Delaware Military Academy on Friday night at Baynard Stadium, 45-14. DMA jumped out to an early 10-0 lead after one quarter before exploding for 28 points in the second quarter giving them a 38-0 advantage at the half. Trailing 45-0 in the fourth, Polytech managed 14 points in the final stanza but it wasn’t enough to build a comeback. The Panthers now stand at 0-6 on the year, and are back in action next Friday night hosting Sussex Tech for Polytech’s homecoming game.
